Create 

Using a pair of square brackets to denote the empty list: []

Using square brackets, separating items with commas: [a], [a, b, c]

Using a list comprehension: [x for x in iterable]
List comprehension is an elegant and concise way to create a new list from an existing list in Python.


Using the type constructor: list() or list(iterable)

Access element
list[index-from-0]
list[negative-index-from--1]

slice 
list[start:end]
list[start:]
list[:end]
list[:]
Loop through

Change element 
list[index] = element

Add element
append(element)

Insert at location
insert(index, element), other element will be shift
list[start:end] = [list,items]

Concat list
extend([list,items])
extend will add all items into the list, list.extend([a,b,c]) [..., a, b, c]
append will add any arg into the list as a whole list.append([a,b,c]) [..., [a,b,c]]

Delete element by index
del (access elemnt)

delete by element
list.remove(element)

delete by index
list.pop(index)

clear list
list.clear()
